      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "NOIR (5) is a fast dog well performed over the sprint races. Filled the minor placings over 401m at Richmond (22.96) in a Grade 4/5 but is better placed at the shorter trip here. Has a strong record at this distance including three wins. Good beginner but will need a little luck from a middle draw. Rates highly and will give a great sight. SHE WILL KICK (1) boasts strong form at this course and distance having won five times from nine starts. Was out of the placings last time (22.66) at this track in a Grade 5, finishing fifth and beaten 6 lengths. Makes strong appeal on best. JUST KEN (2) was a fast winner last time with a dominant 6 lengths win (22.12) at this track. Has a good record here including two wins. Capable of going well again. CHUTZPAH (8) looks an each-way chance.",
